<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4879] CQL help in trunk/doc/cql3/CQL.textile outdated</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4879</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/doc/cql3/CQL.textile&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/doc/cql3/CQL.textile&lt;/a&gt; doesn&apos;t include the new create keyspace syntax or the collections. Last time, I updated the CQL.textile for Paul Cannon to review. Want me to do it again? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BNR-like formatting needs to be replaced, right?, because the brackets now have literal meaning. I test-applied this custom formatting to commands and it seems ok: Uppercase means literal (lowercase nonliteral), italics mean optional, the | symbol means OR, ... means repeatable. The ... in italics doesn&apos;t strictly explain things like nested &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;...&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; does, but it&apos;s easier on the eyes and loosely understandable. Any doubt could be erased by examples, I think. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
